<br>
Actually, the guy said that the pouch needed the three items (ring, idol, insignia) in order to FUNCTION. He said nothing about combining them inside of it.<br>
<br>
1: Seems to me the pouch won't combine anything unless you have those other three items on your person. Try combining different seals in the pouch while you have the idol, ring and insignia on your person.<br>
<br>
2: Second option could be that you combine one of the three items (ring, idol, insignia) in the pouch along with 3 seals. This combine would happen 3 times, covering all three items and all 9 seals, and result in 3 new items and at least the pouch. More than likely you'd get the idol, ring and insignia back as well, combine one of them with the three new seal-combo's and then take that final combined seal, the idol, ring and insignia and end up with the final key. ???<br>
<br>
3: Also possible the pouch itself is the key and you simply need put the idol, ring and insignia inside of it for it to succeed in opening a door. Try identifying the pouch with the three items inside of it. We know &quot;no drop&quot; flags change on containers when &quot;no drop&quot; items are placed inside, or removed. It's quite possible this pouch has a hidden flag/name that changes when those three items are inside of it.<br>
<br>
4: Then again, it could just be that the items weren't combined at the right place and time.<br>
<br>
